      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "IMPACT OF THE INFLATION REDUCTION ACT",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Democrats‚Äô Inflation Reduction Act (IRA), signed into law last month by President Joe Biden, could help matters by theoretically cutting out the PBM middlemen in some instances. That‚Äôs because Medicare will no longer be barred by federal law from negotiating drug prices directly with manufacturers. But the provision ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "only covers",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
