          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " a small number of older drugs, and it will be implemented on a delayed timeline.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "To make matters worse, the IRA helps the PBM industry by once again ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "delaying",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.kff.org/medicare/issue-brief/how-will-the-prescription-drug-provisions-in-the-inflation-reduction-act-affect-medicare-beneficiaries/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " implementation of a Trump-era rule that would scrap the so-called ‚Äúsafe harbor‚Äù that protects PBMs from federal anti-kickback laws and allows them to continue raking in rebates from Medicare‚Äôs prescription drug benefit plans.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
